<recipe>
<title>
Smoked Sausage and Peppers
</title>
<details>

</details>
<ingredients>
1 T . olive oil
4 bell peppers sliced
1 small white onion sliced
1 package Hillshire Farm Smoked Sausage sliced
2 cloves garlic minced
1 oz package spaghetti 12-16 .
Parmesan cheese grated
</ingredients>
<instructions>
Cook spaghetti according to package instructions.
Meanwhile, heat large skillet over medium-low heat.
Add olive oil, and swirl to coat pan.
Stir in bell peppers and onion.
Cook peppers and onion until onion starts to turn translucent.
Stir in Hillshire Farm Smoked Sausage.
Cook until onion is translucent, peppers have softened, and sausage is heated through.
Add in garlic, tossing to combine.
Serve sausage and peppers over spaghetti, and top with parmesan before serving.
</instructions>
</recipe>
